Cloakfox: register about:cloakfox + add browser/components/cloakfox/ to build.

Three tiny hooks into the Firefox tree to register the native settings page:

  1. browser/components/moz.build: add "cloakfox" to DIRS so the new
     additions/browser/components/cloakfox/ directory gets built.

  2. browser/components/about/components.conf: add 'cloakfox' to pages
     list so AboutRedirector knows the URI exists.

  3. browser/components/about/AboutRedirector.cpp: add kRedirMap entry
     mapping about:cloakfox -> chrome://browser/content/cloakfox/settings.html
     with IS_SECURE_CHROME_UI so the page can write prefs with parent
     authority (fixes the class of bug that made setHttp2Profile silently
     no-op from the extension).

All other Cloakfox settings-page code lives in
additions/browser/components/cloakfox/ — no other Firefox files touched.

--- a/browser/components/moz.build
+++ b/browser/components/moz.build
@@ -28,6 +28,7 @@
 DIRS += [
     "about",
     "aboutlogins",
+    "cloakfox",
     "aboutwelcome",
     "asrouter",
     "attribution",
--- a/browser/components/about/components.conf
+++ b/browser/components/about/components.conf
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@

 pages = [
     'asrouter',
+    'cloakfox',
     'blocked',
     'certerror',
     'downloads',
--- a/browser/components/about/AboutRedirector.cpp
+++ b/browser/components/about/AboutRedirector.cpp
@@ -63,6 +63,11 @@
     {"framecrashed", "chrome://browser/content/aboutFrameCrashed.html",
      nsIAboutModule::URI_SAFE_FOR_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT |
          nsIAboutModule::URI_CAN_LOAD_IN_CHILD |
          nsIAboutModule::HIDE_FROM_ABOUTABOUT},
+    // Cloakfox: native settings page. IS_SECURE_CHROME_UI grants the
+    // page Services.prefs write authority — needed so per-container
+    // seeds can be persisted from the UI. The page loads in the parent
+    // process; URI_MUST_LOAD_IN_CHILD would force a child process and
+    // break chrome-priv access. Extension navigation is bridged via
+    // the cloakfox.openSettings WebExtensions API (chrome scope).
+    {"cloakfox", "chrome://browser/content/cloakfox/settings.html",
+     nsIAboutModule::ALLOW_SCRIPT | nsIAboutModule::IS_SECURE_CHROME_UI},
     {"logins", "chrome://browser/content/aboutlogins/aboutLogins.html",
      nsIAboutModule::ALLOW_SCRIPT | nsIAboutModule::URI_MUST_LOAD_IN_CHILD |
          nsIAboutModule::URI_CAN_LOAD_IN_PRIVILEGEDABOUT_PROCESS |
